reviewText:
You play as a butcher who pretends to be a surgeon, but not an ordinary surgeon, it's a surgeon that has only one hand, wears no gloves and has the manual dexterity of a 3 year old kid!

PROS:
- You may learn something about the position of your guts;
- You'll have an idea about how it feels to control a mechanical hand, like those used by people who had an amputed arm. But worse;
- You may fulfill your sadistic instincts by killing your patients with surgical tools;
- You may hit yourself with your own anesthesia syringe, which will make your vision psychodelic.

CONS:
- Controls are awful, VERY awful. Five keys on the keyboard control the closing of your fingers and the mouse will control the movement of your hand, just like a remote-controlled robotic hand would be;
- There's no automatic adjustment of the objects to your hand, which means that you'll pick up objects any way you can, they will never be in the right position and will easily fall from your hand, again similar to a mechanical hand;
- Your arm is always in the same horizontal position and will get in the way often;
- If you drop something on the far corner of the table or let it fall to the ground you can't reach it anymore, it's lost forever;
- It's too difficult to succeed, but possible if you try very, very hard and have a lot of patience (I don't);
- Your patients are completely sedated and won't react to your sadism in case you like this kind of thing;
- Your patients basically die by blood loss (there's a blood counter measuring how near it is to death), so whatever you do will have the same effect. The only difference is the speed of bleeding.

CONCLUSION:
Initiallly fun because of the absurdities, but infuriating thereafter. I can't recommend.
